                    <span>This book is very complete indeed, but it assumes you already know a fair bit about electronic circuitry.  As a computer programmer with little electronics experience, I first had to read up on basic electronics.  Also, some sections could have been easier to understand if there was more supporting details or examples.  However, the book did answer most of my questions about the serail port and I was able to complete my programming project on time.  I would rate this book a 3.5 to 4.0</span>
                  
              
